Sentencas: Ba1.0Sr1.0FeO4+delta (BSFO) with A(2)BO(4) structure as a cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs) is synthesized through an ethylene diamine tetraacetic acid (EDTA)-citrate process, and characterized by X-ray diffraction.
Titulo: Characterization of Ba1.0Sr1.0FeO4+δ cathode on La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-δ electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Field emission scanning electron microscopy shows that BSFO cathode is well attached to the La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-delta (LSGM) electrolyte.
Titulo: Characterization of Ba1.0Sr1.0FeO4+δ cathode on La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-δ electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity measured by DC four-probe method increases as the temperature increases.
Titulo: Characterization of Ba1.0Sr1.0FeO4+δ cathode on La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-δ electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A linear relationship between In(sigma T) and 1000/T indicates that the conducting behavior obeys the small polaron conductivity mechanism.
Titulo: Characterization of Ba1.0Sr1.0FeO4+δ cathode on La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-δ electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Electrochemical performance of BSFO cathode on LSGM electrolyte is investigated in the temperature range from 500 degrees C to 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Characterization of Ba1.0Sr1.0FeO4+δ cathode on La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-δ electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The results indicate that oxygen adsorption/dissociation process dominates cathodic reaction.
Titulo: Characterization of Ba1.0Sr1.0FeO4+δ cathode on La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-δ electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Furthermore, the polarization resistance of BSFO cathode decreases with increasing temperature, and declines to 1.42 Omega cm(2) at 800 degrees C. These results show that BSFO can be a promising cathode material used on LSGM electrolyte for IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Characterization of Ba1.0Sr1.0FeO4+δ cathode on La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-δ electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
